[Project Overview and Implementation Guidelines]
- This project prioritizes using APIs to recognize facial images and analyze them to provide physiognomy information.
- Additionally, it emphasizes entertaining and engaging translations and presentations of the analysis results to end users.
- The project follows Domain-Driven Design (DDD) principles, distinctly separating domain responsibilities to maximize maintainability and extensibility.
- Major domains include face-recognition, physiognomy-analysis, and user authentication and management.
- The architecture is API-driven with a focus on domain modularity and independence.

